quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  22,24,"For they are guided to goodly speech, and they shall be guided to the path of Him who is worthy of all praise (the All-laudable or Glorious One)"
  22,25,"Verily, those who disbelieve and bar men from AllahÂ´s path and from the Sacred Place of Worship, which We have appointed for all mankind alike, the dweller therein and the stranger - and he who desires therein profanity or injustice, We will make hi"
  22,26,"And when We prepared the site (in Mecca) for Abraham as the place of the Holy House, saying, \"Associate naught with Me, but cleanse My House for those who make the rounds, for those who stand to pray, for those who bow, and for those too who prostrat"
  22,27,"And proclaim amongst men the Pilgrimage; they will come to you on foot and on every kind of camel, lean from journeys through distant mountain and deep ravines"
  22,28,"That they may witness things of benefit for them, and that they may mention the name of Allah for (or on) appointed days over the cattle Allah has provided them with (for sacrifice), then eat thereof and feed the distressed ones in want"
  22,29,"Then let them make an end of their self-neglect, and let them pay their vows and go around the ancient House"
  22,30,"That do. And whoever magnifies the sacred things of Allah it is better for him with his Lord. Cattle are lawful for you, except that which has been recited to you. So shun the abomination of idols, and shun lying speech"